In a statement the PSL announced that the draw will be conducted live on on SuperSport 4 at 7pm, reports Phakaaathi.Nedbank Cup draw procedure: All four clubs will be placed in one pot There will be no seeding In each sequence, the first ball to the drawn will be the home club and the second ball their opponent, the away club This process will be repeated until all fixtures are finalisedThe Nedbank Cup quarterfinals will be played on Saturday.Quarterfinals fixtures:Golden Arrows vs Platinum Stars Prince Magogo Stadium 3pm Chippa United vs Jomo Cosmos Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium 3pm Kaizer Chiefs vs SuperSport United FNB Stadium 6pm Orlando Pirates vs Bloemdontein Celtic Orlando Stadium 8.30pm Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za